						               													<description>Recommended for 4 or more players, Per My Last Email is a party game including mature content.   Easy to learn, fast to play, game length can take as little or as much time as you and your friends desire.  Play until the deck runs out, or play for a set amount of time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We all have those things that we want to say in the email chains at work.  From avoiding confrontation with coworkers, to avoiding responsibility with the boss, Per My Last Email lets you say what you really mean.  Using Passive Aggressive and Not-So-Passive Aggressive comments, your job as a player is to avoid responsibility and rule the game.  Employee of the Month never felt so satisfying.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You start the game with each player drawing some Reply Cards.   Then one of the players is selected as the &amp;quot;Boss&amp;quot;, and draws an &amp;quot;Email Card&amp;quot;.   All of the other players who are not the &amp;quot;Boss&amp;quot; then respond to the Email Card with one of their Reply Cards, secretly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;The Boss then reads the Reply Cards and selects the worst excuse to assign the Email Card to.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns as the &amp;quot;Boss&amp;quot; until time is up or the deck is empty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;At the end of the game, the player who has collected the least amount of Email Cards, and has therefore avoided the most responsibility/confrontation Wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
